correctness.rationale: Major schema violations and multiple factual inaccuracies. Key issues: (1) Schema violations: many required numeric fields are null/None, which is not allowed by the schema (e.g., processParameters.pressure.quantityValue.numericValue, thicknessControl.numberofCycles.quantityValue.numericValue, processParameters.filmThickness.quantityValue.numericValue, dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates numeric values, materialProperties.uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, deviceProperties.subthresholdSwing and onOffRatio). plasmaPower is set to null although the property expects an object if present; optional fields with None should be omitted or filled correctly. filmComposition.atomicRatio.value is 'Not Found' but must be a colon-separated ratio string. (2) Factual mismatches: growthPerCycle is given as 0.18 Å for InGaZnO; the article reports ~0.18 nm/cycle for ZnO (DEZ/H2O), whereas IGZO/InZnO GPC is lower and not linear—assigning 0.18 Å to IGZO is incorrect in both compound and unit. (3) Missing/incorrect process parameters traceable from the article: pressure is atmospheric (spatial ALD) but left null; dosing/exposure times were 20–120 ms for both metal and H2O yet left null; number of cycles (e.g., 1400 in Figure 1) and film thickness (e.g., 15 nm IGZO used in TFTs) are available but left null. (4) Supercycle design is populated though the reported process coinjects metal precursors (no supercycle); providing subcycleSequence ['InGaZnO'] is not scientifically coherent. (5) Device properties: field-effect mobility 3.5 cm2/V·s matches; thresholdVoltage is set to −25 V but the text refers to onset voltage at −25 V, not explicitly Vth—this should be clarified. (6) OtherAspects: reproducibility=True is not supported by the text; safety is marked 'Not Found'. To correct: remove or complete optional objects rather than using nulls; set pressure to atmospheric (~760 mmHg), fill dosing times (20–120 ms), provide cycle counts and thickness from the figures, correct GPC (either report ZnO 0.18 nm/cycle under ZnO or leave IGZO GPC unspecified/derived properly), remove supercycleDesign for coinjection S-ALD, and ensure all required numeric fields have valid QUDT-compliant values.

completeness.rationale: Largely incomplete and partially incorrect. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes described in the article (ZnO, InZnO, and IGZO S-ALD) are collapsed into a single IGZO process; separate processes for ZnO (DEZ/H2O, GPC 0.18 nm/cycle) and InZnO are missing. (2) Growth-per-cycle is wrong and misattributed: 0.18 Å is recorded for IGZO, whereas the article reports 0.18 nm/cycle for ZnO (1.8 Å); IGZO GPC is not explicitly given. (3) Many required numeric fields are left null or as “Not Found,” violating schema expectations: pressure (should be atmospheric ~760 mmHg), dosingTime (films used in TFTs had 120 ms exposures; overall range 20–120 ms), purgeTime (SALD does not require purges—should be handled consistently), flowRates (article gives precursor partial pressures: DEZ 1.96 mbar, TMIn up to 0.25 mbar, TEGa up to 0.37 mbar), numberofCycles (e.g., 1400 cycles in Figure 1), and filmThickness (15 nm IGZO used for TFT). (4) Film composition is not captured although provided (e.g., Ga/(In+Ga+Zn)=8% and In/(In+Ga+Zn)=20% for the TFT device); atomicRatio/value and elementalConcentration are left empty. (5) SupercycleDesign is populated though not applicable to coinjected SALD; plasmaPower, subthresholdSwing, onOffRatio, reactor name/manufacturer are included with null/placeholder values instead of being omitted. (6) While nucleationPeriod ~200 cycles and device metrics (μFE ≈ 3.5 cm2/V·s, Vth ≈ −25 V) are correct, overall the extraction has many missing/incorrect fields and weak traceability. Properties to add/review: separate processes (ZnO, InZnO, IGZO), correct GPC and units, dosing/exposure times, atmospheric pressure, partial pressures, cycles and thickness (15 nm), and composition percentages/ratios; remove or properly justify non-applicable fields (purge, supercycle, plasma).
